{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AK2m8K63hZ7nNdiiMH14E2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# `cloche init` Update Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→`cloche init` is out of date. It does not create `config.toml`, `host.cloche`,\n     9→`scripts/`, or `version`. Its `.gitignore` strategy inverts the right default: it\n    10→ignores `.cloche/*/` then negates specific subdirectories, which means any new\n    11→directory added to `.cloche/` is accidentally ignored until explicitly whitelisted.\n    12→\n    13→## New `.gitignore` strategy\n    14→\n    15→Track everything in `.cloche/` by default. Explicitly ignore only runtime artifacts\n    16→(per-run output directories and transient counters).\n    17→\n    18→```\n    19→# Cloche runtime artifacts\n    20→.cloche/*-*-*/\n    21→.cloche/run-*/\n    22→.cloche/attempt_count/\n    23→.gitworktrees/\n    24→```\n    25→\n    26→**Pattern rationale:**\n    27→\n    28→- `.cloche/*-*-*/` — matches all named run output dirs (`develop-bold-hawk/`,\n    29→  `orchestrate-bright-reef/`, etc.). Run IDs are always `<workflow>-<adj>-<noun>`,\n    30→  so any `.cloche/` subdirectory with two or more hyphens is a run artifact.\n    31→  Config directories (`prompts/`, `overrides/`, `scripts/`, `evolution/`) have no\n    32→  hyphens and are unaffected.\n    33→- `.cloche/run-*/` — legacy numeric run output dirs (`run-1772044065239145675/`).\n    34→- `.cloche/attempt_count/` — runtime step-attempt counters written by the agent.\n    35→- `.gitworktrees/` — existing entry, unchanged.\n    36→\n    37→The old entries (`.cloche/*/`, negation rules) are removed when found.\n    38→\n    39→## Conflict safety\n    40→\n    41→Containers write only to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` (their own run directory, which\n    42→is gitignored). Self-reflection and prompt curation run in the daemon process and write\n    43→to committed paths (`.cloche/prompts/`, `.cloche/version`). No container will modify\n    44→committed `.cloche/` files. No merge conflicts.\n    45→\n    46→## Files created by `cloche init`\n    47→\n    48→All files are skipped (with a message) if they already exist.\n    49→\n    50→```\n    51→.cloche/\n    52→  config.toml          # project settings (new)\n    53→  version              # project version counter, content: \"1\" (new)\n    54→  <workflow>.cloche    # container workflow definition (existing)\n    55→  host.cloche          # host orchestration workflow (new)\n    56→  Dockerfile           # container image (existing)\n    57→  prompts/\n    58→    implement.md       # (existing)\n    59→    fix.md             # (existing)\n    60→    update-docs.md     # (existing)\n    61→  scripts/\n    62→    prepare-prompt.sh  # host step: generates prompt from task env vars (new)\n    63→  overrides/           # (existing, directory only)\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→### `config.toml` content\n    67→\n    68→```toml\n    69→# Cloche project configuration\n    70→\n    71→[orchestration]\n    72→enabled     = false\n    73→concurrency = 1\n    74→workflow    = \"develop\"\n    75→# tracker = \"beads\"\n    76→\n    77→[evolution]\n    78→enabled            = true\n    79→debounce_seconds   = 30\n    80→min_confidence     = \"medium\"\n    81→max_prompt_bullets = 50\n    82→```\n    83→\n    84→### `version` content\n    85→\n    86→```\n    87→1\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→### `host.cloche` content\n    91→\n    92→See host workflow design doc. The default replicates current hard-coded behavior:\n    93→prepare a prompt with a shell script, then dispatch the container workflow.\n    94→\n    95→### `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` content\n    96→\n    97→```bash\n    98→#!/usr/bin/env bash\n    99→# Default prompt generator.\n   100→# Writes the task prompt to stdout and to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT.\n   101→set -euo pipefail\n   102→\n   103→prompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n   104→\n   105→${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n   106→\n   107→echo \"$prompt\"\n   108→[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n   109→```\n   110→\n   111→Created with mode `0755`.\n   112→\n   113→## Next steps output\n   114→\n   115→Updated `cloche init` output:\n   116→\n   117→```\n   118→Initialized Cloche project in <name>\n   119→\n   120→Next steps:\n   121→  1. Edit .cloche/config.toml    — enable orchestration, set concurrency\n   122→  2. Edit .cloche/<workflow>.cloche — adjust the test command for your project\n   123→  3. Edit .cloche/Dockerfile     — add your project's dependencies\n   124→  4. Edit .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh — customize prompt generation\n   125→  5. Add container-specific overrides to .cloche/overrides/ (e.g. CLAUDE.md)\n   126→  6. docker build -t cloche-agent -f .cloche/Dockerfile .\n   127→  7. cloche run --workflow <workflow> --prompt \"...\"\n   128→```\n   129→\n   130→## Code changes\n   131→\n   132→| File | Change |\n   133→|------|--------|\n   134→| `cmd/cloche/init.go` | Add `config.toml`, `version`, `host.cloche`, `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` to file list; create `scripts/` dir; rewrite `addGitignoreEntries` call with new pattern set |\n   135→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01K3mPSwo3EPS2mfw1nRbKQ1","session_id":"7a2e9815-bb08-4e95-8216-1026709d7541","uuid":"769efb53-ac46-4330-b917-5191e6b8a06f"}
