{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K3mPSwo3EPS2mfw1nRbKQ1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH RESULTS\n\n### 1. `cloche init` Command Implementation\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` (lines 142-236)\n\nThe `cmdInit` function implements the full initialization command with support for custom workflow name and base image:\n\n- **Function signature:** `func cmdInit(args []string)`\n- **Supported flags:**\n  - `--workflow` (default: \"develop\")\n  - `--base-image` (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n- **Creates directories:** `.cloche`, `.cloche/prompts`, `.cloche/overrides`, `.cloche/scripts`\n- **Writes files:**\n  - `<workflow>.cloche` — workflow DSL file\n  - `Dockerfile` — container image definition\n  - `config.toml` — project configuration\n  - `prompts/implement.md` — implement prompt template\n  - `prompts/fix.md` — fix prompt template\n  - `prompts/update-docs.md` — documentation update prompt\n  - `version` — contains \"1\\n\"\n  - `host.cloche` — host orchestration workflow\n  - `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` — shell script for prompt generation (executable mode 0755)\n\n**Related test file:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init_test.go` (244 lines)\n- Tests default flags, custom flags, existing file skipping, gitignore entries, version content, prepare-prompt permissions, and workflow template structure\n\n### 2. Config Package (`internal/config`)\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` (118 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/config/config_test.go` (141 lines)\n\n**Key structures:**\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Daemon        DaemonConfig        `toml:\"daemon\"`\n    Evolution     EvolutionConfig     `toml:\"evolution\"`\n    Orchestration OrchestrationConfig `toml:\"orchestration\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Loading functions:**\n- `Load(projectDir string)` — reads `<projectDir>/